What YouTube Ads Say About Your Online Habits

Whats going on with this data?

This report investigates the types of YouTube ads that are most commonly recommended and when they appear. The data was collected through direct logging of observed ads over time.

Most Frequent Ad Categories

The bar chart above shows that Food, Sports, and Technology are the most commonly recommended YouTube ad categories, based on observational data. This suggests that advertisers in these industries are targeting a wide audience, potentially based on viewer preferences or time of day.

Ad Appearance Over the Day

This line plot indicates that most YouTube ads appear during the late afternoon and evening hours, peaking around 7 PM. This likely reflects increased viewer activity after work or school hours a prime time for advertisers to engage users.

Contextual Word Count by Ad Category

Here, we compare how many words appeared in the video description or context where the ad was shown. Gaming ads tend to appear in videos with slightly more descriptive context, whereas most other categories have uniformly short contexts possibly due to appearing in shorts or brief clips.

Conclusion

This observational dataset highlights patterns in YouTube advertising exposure. Users are frequently targeted by food and tech ads, especially in the evening, and ad context varies with category.
